<%- layout('layouts/boilerplate')%>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/footerlinks.css">

<div class="about-wrapper container py-5">

  <!-- Title Section -->
  <div class="text-center mb-5 fade-slide">
    <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold about-title">Documentation</h1>
    <p class="lead text-muted about-subtitle">
      Everything you need to understand, use, and integrate WhatIfWorld effectively.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Introduction -->
  <div class="glass-card p-4 mb-5 fade-up">
    <h4 class="fw-bold">Overview</h4>
    <p class="text-muted mt-2">
      WhatIfWorld is an AI-powered scenario prediction platform that allows users
      to explore “What If?” situations across multiple domains like environment,
      politics, economy, health, technology, education, and society.  
      This documentation will guide you through the platform’s features,
      architecture, workflow, user interaction, and community components.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Documentation Sections -->
  <div class="row g-4">

    <!-- Section 1: How It Works -->
    <div class="col-lg-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">1. How WhatIfWorld Works</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          <strong>Step 1:</strong> User enters a “What If?” scenario.  
          <strong>Step 2:</strong> AI validates the scenario for clarity and safety.  
          <strong>Step 3:</strong> Valid input is analyzed using advanced AI models.  
          <strong>Step 4:</strong> The system generates:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-muted">
          <li>Probability score</li>
          <li>Key implications</li>
          <li>Potential challenges</li>
          <li>Graphical charts & visualizations</li>
          <li>Domain-specific impact analysis</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted">
          <strong>Step 5:</strong> User can download or share results to the community.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 2: Features -->
    <div class="col-lg-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">2. Key Features</h4>
        <ul class="text-muted mt-2">
          <li>AI-generated predictions & probability scoring</li>
          <li>Multi-domain impact breakdown</li>
          <li>Downloadable reports and charts</li>
          <li>Community posting, liking, commenting & sharing</li>
          <li>Scenario validation (AI-powered)</li>
          <li>Clean, user-friendly UI with immediate results</li>
          <li>Upcoming: Marketplace, advanced commenting, mobile app</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 3: Supported Domains -->
    <div class="col-lg-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">3. Supported Domains</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">Scenarios can be analyzed in:</p>
        <ul class="text-muted">
          <li>Environment</li>
          <li>Health</li>
          <li>Economy</li>
          <li>Politics</li>
          <li>Technology</li>
          <li>Education</li>
          <li>Society</li>
          <li>Or all domains at once</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 4: AI System -->
    <div class="col-lg-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">4. AI Engine & Prediction Model</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          WhatIfWorld currently uses the <strong>Cerebras AI Model</strong> 
          for generating predictions. The model is trained on diverse datasets 
          and generates insights based on patterns learned during training.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted">
          ⚠️ The predictions are best-effort and not real-world guarantees.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 5: Scenario Validation -->
    <div class="col-lg-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">5. Scenario Validation System</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          Before generating predictions, AI checks:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-muted">
          <li>If the scenario is clearly written</li>
          <li>If it follows a valid “What If…?” structure</li>
          <li>If it contains harmful or unsafe content</li>
          <li>If it can be analyzed meaningfully</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Improper scenarios are rejected with an error message.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 6: Community System -->
    <div class="col-lg-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">6. Community Features</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">Users can:</p>
        <ul class="text-muted">
          <li>Post their scenario results</li>
          <li>Like, comment, and share posts</li>
          <li>View other users’ predictions</li>
          <li>Delete their own posts and comments</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Guest users can view the community but cannot interact.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 7: Account Requirements -->
    <div class="col-lg-6 fade-up">
  <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
    <h4 class="fw-bold">7. Accounts & Authentication</h4>
    <p class="text-muted mt-2">
      Users must be logged in to create scenarios, generate predictions, download results,
      or share posts in the community.
    </p>
    <p class="text-muted">
      We support multiple authentication methods, including 
      <strong>email login</strong> and <strong>Google Sign-In / Sign-Up</strong> for quick and secure access.
    </p>
    <p class="text-muted">
      Account deletion is not available yet, but the feature will be added soon.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>


    <!-- Section 8: Download System -->
    <div class="col-lg-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">8. Downloading Results</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          Users can download:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-muted">
          <li>Prediction summary</li>
          <li>Charts and graphs</li>
          <li>Domain-based analysis</li>
          <li>Full PDF-style reports</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 9: Future Enhancements -->
    <div class="col-12 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">9. Upcoming Enhancements</h4>
        <ul class="text-muted mt-2">
          <li>Mobile app for Android & iOS</li>
          <li>Scenario marketplace</li>
          <li>Creator analytics & tools</li>
          <li>Advanced commenting system</li>
          <li>Follow & followers system</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- Footer Note -->
  <div class="mt-5 fade-slide glass-card p-4">
    <h3 class="fw-bold text-center">Built for Thinkers, Dreamers, and Innovators</h3>
    <p class="text-muted text-center mt-3 mb-0" style="max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto;">
      This documentation will continue to grow as WhatIfWorld evolves with new 
      features and possibilities. Thank you for exploring the future with us.
    </p>
  </div>

</div>

